    "note": "Food security in Jamaica, measured as calorie consumption, moves with money sent home. Tracing the two series from 1976 to 2019, the study finds they rise together over the long run and that the relationship runs in both directions, each feeding the other. Remittances are not only a cushion for hard weeks. Over decades they help decide what reaches the family table.",
