    "note": "Comoros lives across two shores. Roughly 850,000 people are at home on the islands, while around 400,000 Comorians live abroad, some 300,000 of them in France, and what they send back amounts to about a fifth of GDP, the safety net many households actually stand on. In June 2025 the UN Economic Commission for Africa and the government brought ministries, the Central Bank, commercial banks, and diaspora associations around one table in Moroni to start steering part of these flows toward productive investment, the first architecture for a diaspora engagement policy the country does not yet have. For the first time, the money from away is being written into the national plan.",
